Ten deputies have been placed on leave after a video emerged showing them punching and kicking an alleged horse thief for two minutes following a chase through the California desert .
In the video , captured by an NBC helicopter , Francis Pusok , 30 , is seen falling off the horse he was suspected of stealing after being pursued several miles by the San Bernardino County officers .
Seconds later , two deputies catch up to him and stun him with their Tasers .
